# Ao Horoscope (`ao-horoscope`)

## Repo shape

- **`admin-dashboard2/`**: Next.js admin + API + Postgres (Supabase). Production: `https://astradailyadmin.org`.
- **`portfolio/`**: Next.js public site. Production: `https://astradaily.app`. Uses `POST /api/track` which proxies to admin’s public analytics endpoint.
- **`mobile/`**: Expo / React Native app.

Read **`AGENTS.md`** at repo root first; **`PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md`** has the full handoff (migrations, analytics, subtree recovery).

## Git rules (critical)

- **Ask the user before `git commit`.**
- **Ask the user before any `git push`**, including **`git subtree push`**.
- This is a **monorepo**, but **deploy repos are separate**. Do **not** push the whole monorepo to `admindashboard` / `AstraDailyPortfolio` / mobile repo.
- Use **`git subtree push --prefix=<folder> <remote> main`** (see `AGENTS.md` for remote names).
- If subtree push is **rejected (non-fast-forward)**, use the **fetch + subtree split + merge with `--allow-unrelated-histories` + push** flow from **`PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md`** — do not rewrite remote history without explicit user approval.

## Product facts

- Analytics storage: **`PortfolioEvent`** in Supabase; buckets use **`Asia/Kathmandu`**.
- Portfolio production needs **`ASTRADAILY_API_BASE_URL=https://astradailyadmin.org`** (or your admin URL) for tracking proxy.

## Dev sharp edges

- If Next.js infers the **wrong workspace root** (multiple `package-lock.json` upstream), **`turbopack.root`** should be pinned in that app’s `next.config` so `app/` resolves correctly.
